# PROJECT_CONTEXT.md maintenance

After completing any plan, feature, bugfix, API change, test count change, or architectural refactor, update [PROJECT_CONTEXT.md](../PROJECT_CONTEXT.md) as part of definition of done (alongside passing tests).

## When to update

- Plan implementation completed
- New or changed API endpoints
- Pipeline or extraction logic changes
- Test baseline changes
- New known bugs or resolved quirks
- Day/status roadmap shifts (Done / In Progress / To Do)

## What to update

1. **Last Updated** date at the top
2. **Changelog (recent)** — prepend 1–3 bullets for what changed
3. Any affected sections: §2 endpoints, §4 status, §7 tests, §6 quirks, §5 milestones

## Rules

- Do not duplicate entire README; patch only changed sections
- Skip update for trivial edits (typos, comments-only)
- Preserve vision language: HealthLens is a **Personal Health Intelligence System**, not a "report summarizer"
- Separate **shipped vs planned**: do not mark React, MongoDB, JWT, or Gemini as done until code exists in the repo
